Finally got to try this place but honestly a little surprised by the price...then remembered that this is no typical hotdog and sausages. Went for a gourmet mango jalapeno sausage with onion and sauerkraut...but my mistake for getting sauerkraut without really knowing what it is. More sour than I thought so I ended up taking it off my hotdog. But the onion was really good with it and probably the sweet peppers would've been good too.

Finally, the wagyu. Honestly, I didn't expect much out of this dish because we were ordering steak from a pasta shop, but my oh my, how I was so very wrong. The meat was so soft and tender, we kept saying it was like biting into a gummy bear. It was perfectly seasoned and cooked to a perfect medium rare. Again, I'm salivating thinking about this dish. But at $150, I probably wouldn't order this again.
